nfirms third case of coronavirus infection |website=N1 HR |language=hr |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226181744/http://hr.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a486123/Croatia-confirms-third-case-of-coronavirus-infection.html |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2020, a cluster of cases were reported in numerous Croatian cities. On 12 March, the first recovery was reported, and on 18 March the first death from the virus was confirmed. On 19 March, the number of recorded cases surpassed 100. On 21 March, it surpassed 200. On 25 March, it surpassed 400. On 31 March, it surpassed 800. The pandemic in Croatia occurred during the [[Presidency of the Council of the European Union|Croatian Presidency]] of the [[Council of the European Union]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/policies/covid-19-coronavirus-outbreak/ |title=COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak |website=consilium.europa.eu |access-date=31 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330103912/https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/policies/covid-19-coronavirus-outbreak/ |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, an [[2020 Zagreb earthquake|intense earthquake hit Zagreb]], the capital of Croatia, causing problems in enforcement of [[social distancing]] measures set out by the [[Government of Croatia|Government]]. The earthquake could also be felt across much of Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Hungary, Slovenia, and Austria.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/snazni-potresi-uzdrmali-zagreb-prvo-podrhtavanje-zabiljezeno-u-624-drugo-pola-sata-kasnije-gradani-na-ulicama-stete-ogromne-poginula-curica-15/10120042/ |title=SNA\u017dNI POTRESI UZDRMALI ZAGREB Prvo podrhtavanje zabilje\u017eeno u 6.24, drugo pola sata kasnije, gra\u0111ani na ulicama, \u0161tete ogromne, poginula curica (15) |website=Jutarnji List |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322082628/https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/snazni-potresi-uzdrmali-zagreb-prvo-podrhtavanje-zabiljezeno-u-624-drugo-pola-sata-kasnije-gradani-na-ulicama-stete-ogromne-poginula-curica-15/10120042/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timeout.com/croatia/news/large-earthquake-hits-zagreb-032220 |title=Large earthquake hits Zagreb |website=timeout.com |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322084509/https://www.timeout.com/croatia/news/large-earthquake-hits-zagreb-032220 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Oxford University]], as of 24 March, Croatia is the country with the world's strictest restrictions and measures for infection reduction in relation to the number of infected.<ref>{{cite news |last=Veljkovi\u0107 |first=Sandra |url=https://m.vecernji.hr/vijesti/oxford-hrvatska-ima-najstroze-mjere-u-europi-iza-su-samo-srbija-i-sirija-1389281 |title=Oxford: Hrvatska ima najstro\u017ee mjere u Europi. Bero\u0161: Pa\u017eljivo balansiramo |date=26 March 2020 |work=Ve\u010dernji list |url-status=live |language=Croatian |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329150316/https://m.vecernji.hr/vijesti/oxford-hrvatska-ima-najstroze-mjere-u-europi-iza-su-samo-srbija-i-sirija-1389281 |archive-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe government set up a website for all information about the virus and a new phone line 113 that has volunteers answering questions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtl.hr/vijesti-hr/koronavirus/3665535/hrvatska-ima-12-novih-bolesnika-81-zarazenih-ukupno-situacija-u-europi-nije-dobra/ |title=Koronavirusom zara\u017eena 81 osoba! Za gra\u0111ane otvorena linija 113, u kr\u0161enju izolacije uhva\u0107ene 132 osobe |last=N.C. |date=18 March 2020 |website=rtl.hr |language=hr |url-status=live |access-date=19 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210451/https://www.rtl.hr/vijesti-hr/koronavirus/3665535/hrvatska-ima-12-novih-bolesnika-81-zarazenih-ukupno-situacija-u-europi-nije-dobra/ |archive-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Cyprus ===\n<!-- \nPlease also edit [[2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Asia#Cyprus]] to make the information the same\nAlso, do not remove the Northern Cyprus link, the Cyprus article doesn't talk about cases in Northern Cyprus!\n -->\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cyprus|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Northern Cyprus|l2=Northern Cyprus}}\nOn 9 March, [[Cyprus]] confirmed its first two cases, one in Nicosia and one in Limassol.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AFP/status/1237044503464288261 |title=#BREAKING Cyprus reports 2 coronavirus cases, all EU states now hitpic.twitter.com/FBQYaTdUbK |date=9 March 2020 |website=@AFP |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309160200/https://twitter.com/AFP/status/1237044503464288261 |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cyprus-mail.com/2020/03/09/breaking-news-two-cases-of-coronavirus-confirmed/ |title=BREAKING NEWS: Two cases of coronavirus confirmed |date=9 March 2020 |via=cyprus-mail.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/09/two-patients-have-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-in-cyprus/ |title=Two patients have tested positive for the coronavirus in Cyprus |work=Daily Cyprus News |url-status=live |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319211123/https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/09/two-patients-have-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-in-cyprus/ |archive-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Czech Republic ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n[[File:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|thumb|210px|It is forbidden to enter front section of buses of the [[Prague Integrated Transport|Prague Public Transport]] during the pandemic (14 March 2020)]]\nThe first case was reported in the country on 1 March.<ref name=\"CZE\" /> As of 22 March there had been 1120 confirmed cases, with one lethal outcome.<ref name=\"CZE\" />\n\nOn 12 March, the Czech Republic declared a 30-day state of emergency and barred entry to non-residents from China, South Korea, Iran, Italy, Spain, Austria, Germany, Switzerland, Sweden, UK, Norway, Denmark and France.<ref name=\"cnnTBs\">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus: Which countries have travel bans? |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020 |website=cnn.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320091122/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Czech Republic banned people from going out in public without wearing a [[Surgical mask|face mask]] or covering their nose and mouth.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/czechs-get-to-work-making-masks-after-government-decree-coronavirus |title=Czechs get to work making masks after government decree |date=30 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=2 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330235911/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/czechs-get-to-work-making-masks-after-government-decree-coronavirus |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Denmark ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Denmark}}\n{{for|Greenland|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greenland}}\n{{for|Faroe Islands|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Faroe Islands}}\nOn 27 February, Denmark confirmed its first case.<ref>{{cite news |last=Braagaard |first=Natali |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus |title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |work=TV 2 |access-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227054434/https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus |archive-date=27 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\nAs of 16 March, there have been 898 confirmed cases in Denmark, including 11 in the Faroe Islands (see below).<ref name=\"STPS numbers\">{{Cite news |url=https://politi.dk/coronavirus-i-danmark/foelg-smittespredningen-globalt-regionalt-og-lokalt |title=F\u00f8lg smittespredningen globalt, regionalt og lokalt |date=16 March 2020 |work=Styrelsen for Patientsikkerhed ([[Ministry of Health (Denmark)|Ministry of Health]]) |access-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320214647/https://politi.dk/coronavirus-i-danmark/foelg-smittespredningen-globalt-regionalt-og-lokalt |archive-date=20 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nNumerous preventive measures gradually were implemented. Starting on 13 March, schools, universities and similar places were closed, while most people in non-essential functions have been sent home to work.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Svendsen |first=Anders Byskov |url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/politik/corona-tiltag-elever-og-studerende-paa-alle-uddannelsesinstitutioner-sendes-hjem-nu |title=Corona-tiltag: Elever og studerende p\u00e5 alle uddannelsesinstitutioner sendes hjem nu |date=11 March 2020 |work=DR |access-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311195948/https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/politik/corona-tiltag-elever-og-studerende-paa-alle-uddannelsesinstitutioner-sendes-hjem-nu |archive-date=11 March 2020 }}</ref> On 14 March, the borders were closed for all entries, except Danish citizens, people with a residence permit, people with an important reason for visiting, and transport of goods.<ref>{{Cite news |last=M\u00f8ller |first=Albert Schmidt |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-13-statsministeren-lukker-graensen-for-at-bremse-coronavirussen |title=Statsministeren lukker gr\u00e6nsen for at bremse coronavirussen |date=13 March 2020 |work=TV 2 |access-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314180452/https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-13-statsministeren-lukker-graensen-for-at-bremse-coronavirussen |archive-date=14 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=cnnTBs/>\n\n=== Estonia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Estonia}}\nOn 27 February [[Estonia]] confirmed its first case, an Iranian citizen, travelling from Iran via Turkey.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |title=First Coronavirus case found in Estonia |access-date=27 February 2020 |publisher=[[Eesti Rahvusringh\u00e4\u00e4ling|ERR]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227065704/https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 11 March there were 17 confirmed cases in Estonia. 12 of them had returned with the infection from Northern Italy, one from France, one from Iran and one from undisclosed risk area.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.err.ee/1060677/eestis-on-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-kumnel-inimesel |title=Eestis on koroonaviirus tuvastatud k\u00fcmnel inimesel |date=6 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |language=et |trans-title=Ten people have been diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307152100/https://www.err.ee/1060677/eestis-on-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-kumnel-inimesel |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.err.ee/1061912/teisipaevase-seisuga-on-eestis-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-13-inimesel |title=Teisip\u00e4evase seisuga on Eestis koroonaviirus tuvastatud 13 inimesel |date=10 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |language=Estonian |trans-title=As of Tuesday, 13 people have been diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311180618/https://www.err.ee/1061912/teisipaevase-seisuga-on-eestis-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-13-inimesel |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> First two cases of virus transmitting locally were in [[Saaremaa]] after international volleyball competition involving a team from [[Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.err.ee/1062392/three-new-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |title=Three new cases of coronavirus disease confirmed in Estonia |date=11 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |access-date=12 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311204452/https://news.err.ee/1062392/three-new-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFrom 12 March the virus was spreading locally. The number of infected grew fast reaching 109 on 14 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.err.ee/1063959/109-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |title=109 cases of coronavirus disease confirmed in Estonia |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315140308/https://news.err.ee/1063959/109-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Finland ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Finland}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 28 January.<ref>[https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/finlands_first_coronavirus_case_confirmed_in_lapland/11182855 Finland's first coronavirus case confirmed in Lapland]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.helsinkitimes.fi/finland/finland-news/domestic/17272-finland-s-first-coronavirus-patient-began-to-show-symptoms-three-days-ago.html |title=Finland's first coronavirus patient began to show symptoms three days ago |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309215132/https://www.helsinkitimes.fi/finland/finland-news/domestic/17272-finland-s-first-coronavirus-patient-began-to-show-symptoms-three-days-ago.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== France ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n[[File:Super U \u2013 des rayons vides.jpg|thumb|210px|Empty supermarket shelves in [[Annonay]], France, on 14 March 2020.]]\n\nOn 24 January, the first case in Europe was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. Two more cases were confirmed in [[Paris]] by the end of the day, all of them originated from China. A cluster of infections was discovered in Haute-Savoie which originated from a British national who had visited [[Singapore]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux |title=Coronavirus : Que sait-on du cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Bordeaux ? |last=Provenzano |first=Elsa |date=26 January 2020 |website=20 Minutes |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219143036/https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux |archive-date=19 February 2020 |access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-5-nouveaux-cas-en-france-20200208 |title=Coronavirus : 5 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s en France |last=Figaro |first=Le |date=8 February 2020 |website=Le Figaro.fr |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208101615/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-5-nouveaux-cas-en-france-20200208 |archive-date=8 February 2020 |access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":22\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/coronavirus-une-11e-guerison-en-france-plus-aucun-malade-hospitalise-6751169 |title=Coronavirus. Une 11e gu\u00e9rison en France, \" plus aucun malade hospitalis\u00e9 \" |date=24 February 2020 |website=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224202543/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/coronavirus-une-11e-guerison-en-france-plus-aucun-malade-hospitalise-6751169 |archive-date=24 February 2020 |access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 31 January to 9 February, nearly 550 people were repatriated from [[Wuhan]] on a series of evacuation flights arriving at Creil Air Base in [[Oise]] and [[Istres-Le Tub\u00e9 Air Base]] in [[Istres]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.defense.gouv.fr/actualites/international/l-armee-de-l-air-au-service-des-francais |title=L'Arm\u00e9e de l'air au service des Fran\u00e7ais |date=2 February 2020 |website=defense.gouv.fr |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327233053/https://www.defense.gouv.fr/actualites/international/l-armee-de-l-air-au-service-des-francais |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 14 February, an 80-year-old Chinese tourist died in [[Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital]], [[Paris]], marking the first death from COVID-19 in Europe and France.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837 |title=First coronavirus death confirmed in Europe |date=15 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219204410/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837 |archive-date=19 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAccording to regional council president Jean Rottner, the starting point for the first intense wave in Alsace was the Fasting Meeting of the Protestant Free Church of La Porte Ouverte in Mulhouse, with more than 2500 visitors, in mid-February.<ref name=\"faz\">{{Cite news |last=Wiegel |first=Michaela |url=https://www.faz.net/1.6702139 |title=Corona-Krise im Elsass: \"Wir sind unendlich dankbar f\u00fcr die Hilfe aus Deutschland\" |date=2020-03-30 |work=FAZ.NET |access-date=2020-03-30 |last2=Paris |language=de |issn=0174-4909}}</ref>\nOn 12 March, French president Emmanuel Macron announced on public television that all schools and all universities would close from Monday 16 March until further notice. The next day, the prime minister \u00c9douard Philippe banned gatherings of more than 100 people, not including public transportation. The following day, the prime minister ordered the closure of all nonessential public places, including restaurants, caf\u00e9s, cinemas, and discoth\u00e8ques, effective at midnight.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477 |title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions |date=15 March 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320221934/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 14 March, there had been 4,499 confirmed cases (a near-four-fold increase over the number 5 days previously), and 91 deaths in France.<ref>[https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde Infection au nouveau Coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), COVID-19, France et Monde] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321143945/https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde |date=21 March 2020 }} ''www.santepubliquefrance.fr'', accessed 12 March 2020</ref>\n\nAs of 20 March, the number of confirmed cases had risen to 12,612, while the number of deaths reached 450.<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\nAs of March 30, more than six hundred doctors and other medical workers are suing the former Minister of Health and the Prime Minister for \"culpable negligence\" in failing to prepare for the epidemic.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Collins |first=Lauren |url=https://www.newyorker.com/science/medical-dispatch/here-the-terrorists-are-inside-the-french-psychiatrist-who-counsels-crisis-doctors |title=\"Here, the Terrorists Are Inside\": The French Psychiatrist Who Counsels Crisis Doctors |date=2020-03-30 |work=The New Yorker |access-date=2020-03-31 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331155454/https://www.newyorker.com/science/medical-dispatch/here-the-terrorists-are-inside-the-french-psychiatrist-who-counsels-crisis-doctors |archive-date=31 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nUntil 1 April, the daily update of the number of deaths in France included only deaths in hospitals, with deaths in retirement homes or at home not included in the update.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2748183-20200325-coronavirus-nombre-deces-ephad-probablement-beaucoup-plus-lourd-bilan-officiel |title=En Ehpad, le nombre de morts du Covid-19 plus lourd que le bilan officiel |date=2020-03-25 |work=20 minutes |access-date=2020-03-30 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327111304/https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2748183-20200325-coronavirus-nombre-deces-ephad-probablement-beaucoup-plus-lourd-bilan-officiel |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Deaths in retirement homes were included in the reported figures from 2 April, causing totals to increase substantially.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200403-french-hospitals-record-deadliest-day-with-588-coronavirus-deaths|title=French hospitals record deadliest day with 588 coronavirus deaths|date=3 April 2020|publisher=France 24|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Germany ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany}}\n\n=== Greece ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greece}}\nOn 26 February, the first case in Greece was confirmed, a 38-year-old woman from [[Thessaloniki]] who had recently visited [[Northern Italy]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA |title=Greece confirms first coronavirus case |date=26 February 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=26 February 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226113222/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The next day, the first patient's 9-year-old child and another 40-year-old woman, who had travelled to Italy, also tested positive.<ref name=\":172\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-deytero-thetiko-kroysma-stin-ellada-paidi-38hronis |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0394\u03b5\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf \u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 -\u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03af \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 38\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391 |date=27 February 2020 |website=iefimerida.gr |language=el |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227113930/https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-deytero-thetiko-kroysma-stin-ellada-paidi-38hronis |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":83\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-athina-trito-kroysma-stin-ellada-akyronontai-ola-ta-karnabalia |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 -\u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b2\u03ac\u03bb\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391 |date=27 February 2020 |website=iefimerida.gr |language=el |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227114026/https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-athina-trito-kroysma-stin-ellada-akyronontai-ola-ta-karnabalia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":72\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561073/koronoios-tria-kroysmata-stin-el