, 150, 188,240, 349, 534\n|y5= 15, 20, 23, 35, 39, 51, 87, 116, 164, 209, 321, 384, 460, 586, 643\n|y6= 30, 31, 53, 104, 204, 433, 602\n|y7=41,35, 62, 121, 198, 291,440, 571 \n|y1Title=France\n|y2Title=Italy\n|y3Title=Spain\n|y4Title=Germany\n|y5Title=UK\n|y6Title=Korea\n|y7Title=mainland China\n|yGrid= |xGrid= \n}}\n\n== Criticism of response to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic ==\nAlthough by 7 March some European politicians such as France's [[Marine Le Pen]] had called for Europe's internal borders to be temporarily closed,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |title=Coronavirus: European borders likely to remain open despite crisis in Italy, observers say |date=7 March 2020 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315040544/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the [[European Union]] by 13 March continued to reject the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Area|Schengen free travel area]] and introducing border controls with Italy.<ref name=\"dw-schengen\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313142436/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure |date=25 February 2020 |work=Bloomberg |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227122244/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173409/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |title=Commission chief warns against unilateral virus travel bans |date=13 March 2020 |work=[[EURACTIV]] |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195056/https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The deputy leader of the Swiss [[Ticino League]], Lorenzo Quadri, by 29 February had criticised the decision: \"It is alarming that the dogma of wide-open borders is considered a priority.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream |date=26 February 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303055756/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> United States President [[Donald Trump]] said by 12 March the European Union had \"failed to take the same precautions and restrict travel from China and other hot spots\" as the US had implemented.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |title=In dramatic step, Trump restricts travel from Europe to US to fight coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140433/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Trump also said that \"As a result a large number of new clusters in the United States were seeded by travellers from Europe.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: What you need to know about Trump's Europe travel ban |url=https://www.thelocal.dk/20200312/trump-imposes-travel-ban-from-europe-over-coronavirus-outbreak |work=The Local |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> Research on [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|coronavirus genomes]] indicates the majority of COVID-19 cases in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] came from European travelers, rather than directly from China or any other Asian country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Studies Show N.Y. Outbreak Originated in Europe|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/coronavirus-live-updates.html |work=The New York Times |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n\nBy 9 March Czech Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] stated that \"European countries cannot ban the entry of Italian citizens within the Schengen area. The only possible way is to have the Italian prime minister call on his fellow citizens to refrain from traveling to other countries of the European Union.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |title=Czech PM: Italians Should Be Banned From Travelling Due to Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=SchengenVisaInfo.com |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171345/https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland and Denmark announced complete closure of their national borders, the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said by 12 March that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization. Moreover, they have a strong social and economic impact, they disrupt people\u2019s lives and business across the borders.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314202823/https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> European Union leaders condemned the US decision to restrict travel from Europe to the United States. [[European Council]] President [[Charles Michel]] and Ursula von der Leyen said in a joint statement: \"The European Union disapproves of the fact that the US decision to impose a travel ban was taken unilaterally and without consultation.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |date=12 March 2020 |work=Associated Press (AP) |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313140528/https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ursula von der Leyen admitted by 17 March that \"all of us who are not experts initially underestimated the coronavirus.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |title=Politicians 'underestimated' virus threat, von der Leyen admits |date=18 March 2020 |work=Euractiv |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319152350/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Italian government has criticised EU's lack of solidarity with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |title=The EU Is Abandoning Italy in Its Hour of Need |date=14 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315112947/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |date=11 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313000621/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Italy wonders where Europe's solidarity is as coronavirus strains show |date=13 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315154437/https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |title=Italy criticizes EU for not responding its call for help, 'only China responded bilaterally' |date=12 March 2020 |work=CGTN |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316024124/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Politico'' reported on 7 March that \"EU countries have so far refused Italy's plea for help fighting coronavirus, as national capitals worry that they may need to stockpile face masks and other medical gear to help their own citizens, officials and diplomats said.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |title=Europe fails to help Italy in coronavirus fight |date=7 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317055659/https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Maurizio Massari, Italy's ambassador to the EU, said that \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\" /> [[Serbia]]n President [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] said that \"European solidarity does not exist. That was a fairy tale.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |title=China is winning the coronavirus propaganda war |date=18 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203919/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe planned [[NATO]] \u201c[[List of NATO exercises|Defender 2020]]\u201d military exercise in Germany, Poland, and the Baltic states,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |title=How coronavirus derailed the largest Nato exercise in 25 years |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Spectator |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102257/https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the largest NATO war manoeuvres since the end of the [[Cold War]], was to be held on a reduced scale because of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |title=NATO scales down exercises due to coronavirus |date=19 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102254/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]'s general secretary [[Kate Hudson (activist)|Kate Hudson]] critisiced the Defender 2020 exercise: \"In the current public-health crisis, it jeopardises the lives not only of the troops from the US and the many European countries participating but the inhabitants of the countries in which they are operating.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |title=Nato must end 'dangerous and irresponsible' military exercise on Russia's border, campaigners say |date=18 March 2020 |work=Morning Star |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320010441/https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PREPARE]] (EU PREPARE project)\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"OKOpress_Szumowski_EU_claims\">{{cite news | last1= Pa\u0144kowska | first1= Maria | language =pl | title= Szumowski krytykuje UE: 'Nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci'. To wielopi\u0119trowy fa\u0142sz |trans-title = Szumowski criticise the EU: 'There is no European solidarity'. Which is false at many levels<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 2020-03-26 |newspaper= [[OKO.press]] | url= https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |quote= Bo jak by\u015bmy czekali na inne kraje, na Europ\u0119, na \u015bwiat, to by\u015bmy si\u0119 obudzili bez \u015brodk\u00f3w, a dooko\u0142a wszyscy by te \u015brodki sobie zakupili ... \u017beby by\u0142a jasno\u015b\u0107, to nie jest tak, \u017ce my ten sprz\u0119t mamy w Europie, \u017ce s\u0105 jego nieograniczone ilo\u015bci. ... Bo niestety tutaj centralne zakupy zawiod\u0142y, nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci.  |accessdate=2020-03-26 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326225848/https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |archivedate= 2020-03-26 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://systems.jhu.edu/research/public-health/ncov/ ncov \u2013 CSSE] \u2013 Map of the expansion of the virus in Europe and in the world\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe| ]]\n", "name_user": "Ondoro", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStatistics by country and territory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe"}
{"title_page": "Fwupd", "text_new": "{{Confuse|swupd}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Infobox software\n| name = fwupd\n| logo = <!-- Image name is enough -->\n| logo alt = \n| logo caption = \n| screenshot = <!-- Image name is enough -->\n| screenshot alt = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = <!-- Any text here will collapse the screenshot -->\n| author = Richard Hughes<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/>\n| developer = \n| released = {{Start date and age|2015|03|17|df=yes}}<ref name=fwupdreleases>https://github.com/hughsie/fwupd/releases</ref>\n| discontinued = <!-- Set to yes if software is discontinued, otherwise omit -->\n| ver layout = <!-- simple (default) or stacked -->\n| latest release version = 1.4.0\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|04|14|df=yes}}<ref name=fwupdreleases />\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} -->\n| programming language = [[C (programming language)|C]]\n| operating system = [[Linux]]\n| platform = \n| size = \n| language = \n| language count = <!-- Number only -->\n| language footnote = \n| genre = [[firmware]] updates for [[Linux]]-based systems\n| license = LGPL v2.1\n| alexa = \n| website = {{URL|fwupd.org}}\n| repo = {{URL|github.com/fwupd/fwupd/}}\n| standard = \n| AsOf = \n}}\n'''fwupd''' is an [[open-source software|open-source]] [[Daemon (computing)|daemon]] for managing the installation of [[firmware]] updates on [[Linux]]-based systems, developed by [[GNOME]] maintainer Richard Hughes.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/>\n\nIt is designed primarily for servicing the [[Unified Extensible Firmware Interface]] (UEFI) firmware on supported devices via EFI System Resource Table (ESRT) and UEFI Capsule, which is supported in [[Linux kernel]] 4.2 and later. Previously, the initiation of UEFI firmware updates within an operating system could, on most systems, only be performed using [[Microsoft Windows]] or [[DOS]]-specific software. ESRT allows the firmware to expose updatable components to the operating system, which can pass a UEFI capsule with updated firmware for processing and installation on the next boot.<ref name=intel-bfupdates>{{cite web|title=Better Firmware Updates in Linux using UEFI Capsules|url=https://blogs.intel.com/evangelists/2015/06/23/better-firmware-updates-in-linux-using-uefi-capsules/|publisher=Intel|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=phoronix-uefi25>{{cite web|title=Linux BIOS/UEFI Updating Is Going To Get Much Better With UEFI 2.5|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=UEFI-2.5-Better-Linux-Updates|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Linux 4.2 To Support The EFI System Resource Table|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=Linux-4.2-EFI-System-ESRT-Table|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref> Updates can be exposed via a command line tool, or within graphical package managers (such as [[GNOME Software]]) via a [[D-bus]] interface.<ref name=phoronix-fwupd/>\n\n==Linux Vendor Firmware Service==\nThe '''Linux Vendor Firmware Service''' ('''LVFS''') provides resources and support for helping vendors package their firmware updates to support the use of this framework, and serves as an online repository for obtaining these updates.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/><ref name=\"softpedia-1604\">{{cite web|title=Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Might Get the Option of Updating Firmware Directly from the OS|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/ubuntu-16-04-lts-might-get-the-option-of-updating-firmware-directly-from-the-os-498626.shtml|website=Softpedia|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref> To provide a test case on systems where ESRT is not yet supported, fwupd is also able to update firmware on the ColorHug [[color calibration|color calibrator]].<ref name=phoronix-fwupd>{{cite web|title=fwupd: Simple, Open-Source Device Firmware Updating|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=fwupd-UEFI-Firmware-Update|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Adoption==\n[[Fedora (operating system)|Fedora]] 24 supports the use of fwupd.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/> [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] 16.04 LTS also includes it.<ref>https://packages.ubuntu.com/xenial/admin/fwupd</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, it was revealed that Hughes had been working with a [[Dell Inc.|Dell]] developer to test the system on actual hardware, and that its Dell Edge Gateway product will support firmware servicing via fwupd. Hughes reported that the company was also \"considering expanding out the LVFS support to all new models supporting UEFI updates\".<ref name=softpedia-delllfus>{{cite web|title=Linux Users Will Soon Be Able to Update Dell Firmware from Inside the OS|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/linux-users-will-soon-be-able-to-update-dell-firmware-from-inside-the-os-497479.shtml|website=Softpedia|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, [[Lenovo]] joined the project and provides update support for a wide range of their devices.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2018/08/06/please-welcome-lenovo-to-the-lvfs/|title=Please welcome Lenovo to the LVFS \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|website=blogs.gnome.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-04}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, [[Acer Inc.|Acer]] joined the project, with initial support for their Aspire A315 model.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2019/09/11/please-welcome-acer-to-the-lvfs/|title=Please welcome Acer to the LVFS \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|website=blogs.gnome.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-13}}</ref>\n\nStarting from December 2019, [[Google]] requires that firmware updates can be applied with fwupd for certified [[Chromebook|Chromebooks]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2019/11/18/google-and-fwupd/|title=Google and fwupd sitting in a tree \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref>\n\nAll supported devices are [https://fwupd.org/lvfs/devicelist tracked on the lvfs website].\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Free and open-source software}}\n* [[Flashrom]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|fwupd.org}}\n\n{{Linux package management systems}}\n\n[[Category:Applications using D-Bus]]\n[[Category:Firmware]]\n[[Category:Software that uses Meson]]\n[[Category:Unified Extensible Firmware Interface]]\n", "text_old": "{{Confuse|swupd}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Infobox software\n| name = fwupd\n| logo = <!-- Image name is enough -->\n| logo alt = \n| logo caption = \n| screenshot = <!-- Image name is enough -->\n| screenshot alt = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = <!-- Any text here will collapse the screenshot -->\n| author = Richard Hughes<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/>\n| developer = \n| released = {{Start date and age|2015|03|17|df=yes}}<ref name=fwupdreleases>https://github.com/hughsie/fwupd/releases</ref>\n| discontinued = <!-- Set to yes if software is discontinued, otherwise omit -->\n| ver layout = <!-- simple (default) or stacked -->\n| latest release version = 1.3.6\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2019|12|30|df=yes}}<ref name=fwupdreleases />\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} -->\n| programming language = [[C (programming language)|C]]\n| operating system = [[Linux]]\n| platform = \n| size = \n| language = \n| language count = <!-- Number only -->\n| language footnote = \n| genre = [[firmware]] updates for [[Linux]]-based systems\n| license = LGPL v2.1\n| alexa = \n| website = {{URL|fwupd.org}}\n| repo = {{URL|github.com/fwupd/fwupd/}}\n| standard = \n| AsOf = \n}}\n'''fwupd''' is an [[open-source software|open-source]] [[Daemon (computing)|daemon]] for managing the installation of [[firmware]] updates on [[Linux]]-based systems, developed by [[GNOME]] maintainer Richard Hughes.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/>\n\nIt is designed primarily for servicing the [[Unified Extensible Firmware Interface]] (UEFI) firmware on supported devices via EFI System Resource Table (ESRT) and UEFI Capsule, which is supported in [[Linux kernel]] 4.2 and later. Previously, the initiation of UEFI firmware updates within an operating system could, on most systems, only be performed using [[Microsoft Windows]] or [[DOS]]-specific software. ESRT allows the firmware to expose updatable components to the operating system, which can pass a UEFI capsule with updated firmware for processing and installation on the next boot.<ref name=intel-bfupdates>{{cite web|title=Better Firmware Updates in Linux using UEFI Capsules|url=https://blogs.intel.com/evangelists/2015/06/23/better-firmware-updates-in-linux-using-uefi-capsules/|publisher=Intel|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=phoronix-uefi25>{{cite web|title=Linux BIOS/UEFI Updating Is Going To Get Much Better With UEFI 2.5|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=UEFI-2.5-Better-Linux-Updates|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Linux 4.2 To Support The EFI System Resource Table|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=Linux-4.2-EFI-System-ESRT-Table|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref> Updates can be exposed via a command line tool, or within graphical package managers (such as [[GNOME Software]]) via a [[D-bus]] interface.<ref name=phoronix-fwupd/>\n\n==Linux Vendor Firmware Service==\nThe '''Linux Vendor Firmware Service''' ('''LVFS''') provides resources and support for helping vendors package their firmware updates to support the use of this framework, and serves as an online repository for obtaining these updates.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/><ref name=\"softpedia-1604\">{{cite web|title=Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Might Get the Option of Updating Firmware Directly from the OS|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/ubuntu-16-04-lts-might-get-the-option-of-updating-firmware-directly-from-the-os-498626.shtml|website=Softpedia|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref> To provide a test case on systems where ESRT is not yet supported, fwupd is also able to update firmware on the ColorHug [[color calibration|color calibrator]].<ref name=phoronix-fwupd>{{cite web|title=fwupd: Simple, Open-Source Device Firmware Updating|url=https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=news_item&px=fwupd-UEFI-Firmware-Update|website=Phoronix|accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Adoption==\n[[Fedora (operating system)|Fedora]] 24 supports the use of fwupd.<ref name=softpedia-delllfus/> [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] 16.04 LTS also includes it.<ref>https://packages.ubuntu.com/xenial/admin/fwupd</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, it was revealed that Hughes had been working with a [[Dell Inc.|Dell]] developer to test the system on actual hardware, and that its Dell Edge Gateway product will support firmware servicing via fwupd. Hughes reported that the company was also \"considering expanding out the LVFS support to all new models supporting UEFI updates\".<ref name=softpedia-delllfus>{{cite web|title=Linux Users Will Soon Be Able to Update Dell Firmware from Inside the OS|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/linux-users-will-soon-be-able-to-update-dell-firmware-from-inside-the-os-497479.shtml|website=Softpedia|accessdate=9 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, [[Lenovo]] joined the project and provides update support for a wide range of their devices.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2018/08/06/please-welcome-lenovo-to-the-lvfs/|title=Please welcome Lenovo to the LVFS \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|website=blogs.gnome.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-04}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, [[Acer Inc.|Acer]] joined the project, with initial support for their Aspire A315 model.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2019/09/11/please-welcome-acer-to-the-lvfs/|title=Please welcome Acer to the LVFS \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|website=blogs.gnome.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-13}}</ref>\n\nStarting from December 2019, [[Google]] requires that firmware updates can be applied with fwupd for certified [[Chromebook|Chromebooks]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2019/11/18/google-and-fwupd/|title=Google and fwupd sitting in a tree \u2013 Technical Blog of Richard Hughes|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-18}}</ref>\n\nAll supported devices are [https://fwupd.org/lvfs/devicelist tracked on the lvfs website].\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Free and open-source software}}\n* [[Flashrom]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|fwupd.org}}\n\n{{Linux package management systems}}\n\n[[Category:Applications using D-Bus]]\n[[Category:Firmware]]\n[[Category:Software that uses Meson]]\n[[Category:Unified Extensible Firmware Interface]]\n", "name_user": "PieterDeBruijn", "label": "safe", "comment": "version update 1.4.0", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fwupd"}
{"title_page": "REICK (DJ)", "text_new": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:REICK }}\n\n'''[Koushik Mukherjee]''' known professionally as '''[REICK]''' ''(previously went by the stage name Koushik Mukherjee)'' is an [[Indian people|Indian]] [[Disc jockey|DJ]], songwriter and record producer based in [[Kolkata]], [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/koushik-mukherjee-mn0003582679/discography|title=Koushik Mukherjee {{!}} Album Discography|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/4DPP90htu1QIrbeZ6g3OAs|title=REICK|website=Spotify|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> He is best known for his \n\n{{Infobox artist\n| image            = https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Reickshoot1.jpg#/media/File:Reickshoot1.jpg\n| birth_name       = Koushik Mukherjee\n| style            = Dance-Pop, Electronic\n| Instruments      = Piano, Synthesizer, Keyboard\n}}\n\nability to create an unique vibe while performing or producing music. Some of his most popular tracks are \"'''Slow Love'''\" featuring [[Jimmy Burney]] , \"'''There For You'''\" which did turn out to be an important mark to begin his career as a record producer.\n\n== Career ==\nREICK has performed across the country at various clubs, music festivals alongside some of the finest Indian and international artists.\n\nHe has began his career interning with [[The Thrillseekers]] which did help him gain interest and perfect his art for electronic music.\n\nHe made his first official release '''\"There For You\"''' as Koushik Mukherjee which peaked onto #52 rank on Top 100 Electronica charts at [[Beatport]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/there-for-you-mw0003010771|title=There for You - Koushik Mukherjee {{!}} Songs, Reviews, Credits|website=AllMusic|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beatport.com/artist/koushik-mukherjee/580276|title=Koushik Mukherjee Tracks & Releases on Beatport|website=www.beatport.com|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nSuccess came in as he dropped his new single '''[https://fanlink.to/reickmusic \"Slow Love\"]''' under his new stage name '''REICK'''. Slow Love garnered alot of attention with it peaking onto #2 rank on [[ITunes Store|iTunes]] India Dance Charts and #91 on iTunes India charts <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kworb.net/itunes/artist/reick.html|title=REICK Chart Positions on iTunes/Spotify/YouTube|website=kworb.net|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> within the first week of the release. Slow Love has over 1.1 Million views on [[YouTube (channel)|YouTube]]<ref>{{Citation|title=REICK ft. Jimmy Burney - Slow Love (Official Music Video)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9hqVWE8QEA0|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> , and is also being aired on [[VH1 India|Vh1]].\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== '''Singles''' ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Title             \n!Year\n!Album\n!Notes\n|-\n|\"Himalaya\" \ncredited as a co producer\n\nfo inDjnous Tribe along with Dj Harish <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beatport.com/track/himalaya-original-mix/4211508|title=Himalaya (Original Mix) by DJ Harish, Sid & Koushik, InDJnous Tribe on Beatport|website=www.beatport.com|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>    \n|2013  \n|Single \n|\n|-\n|\"There For You\"\ncredited as Koushik Mukherjee <ref>{{Citation|title=\u200eThere For You - Single by Koushik Mukherjee|url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/there-for-you-single/1161489482|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=There For You|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/0mArWEN2kSjLh5hrlCO96Q|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Koushik-Mukherjee-There-For-You/release/9436847|title=Koushik Mukherjee - There For You|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|2016\n|Single  \n|Ranked #52 on Beaport Top 100 Electronica Charts\n|-\n|\"Slow Love\" feat. [[Jimmy Burney]] \ncredited as REICK <ref>{{Citation