nta Maria Church]] Complex, [[Paoay Church]] Complex, San Agustin Church Complex, [[Miagao Church]] Complex, Rice Terraces of the Cordilleras which includes five different rice terrace clusters, Tubbataha Reefs Natural Park, Underground River of Puerto Princesa, and [[Mount Hamiguitan]] Wildlife Sanctaury), '''two UNESCO World Heritage Cities''' ([[Vigan]] and [[Miagao]]), '''one UNESCO Creative City''' ([[Baguio]]), '''three UNESCO Biosphere Reserves''' ([[Palawan]] Biosphere Reserve, [[Albay]] Biosphere Reserve, and [[Puerto Galera]] Biosphere Reserve), '''seven [[List of Ramsar sites in the Philippines|Ramsar Wetland Sites]]''' ([[Las Pi\u00f1as-Para\u00f1aque Critical Habitat and Ecotourism Area|Las Pi\u00f1as-Para\u00f1aque]], [[Naujan Lake National Park|Lake Naujan]], [[Puerto Princesa Subterranean River National Park|Puerto Princesa]], [[Tubbataha Reefs Natural Park|Tubbataha Reefs]], [[Olango Island Wildlife Sanctuary|Olango]], [[Agusan Marsh Wildlife Sanctuary|Agusan Marsh]], and [[Negros Occidental]] Coastal Wetlands), and '''eight [[ASEAN]] Heritage Parks''' (Mount Apo National Park, Mounts Iglit-Baco  National Park, Mount kitanglad  National Park, Mount Makiling  National Park, Tubbataha Reefs Natural Park, Mount Hamiguitan Wildlife Sanctuary, and Timpoong-Hibok-Hibok  National Park) in the Philippines. The last three lists reinforces the title of the Philippines as one of the [[biodiversity hotspot]]s declared by [[Conservation International]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.conservation.org/How/Pages/Hotspots.aspx |title=Why Hotspots Matter - Conservation International |publisher=Conservation.org |date=2015-11-20 |accessdate=2018-03-29}}</ref> The following are the most significant natural and cultural heritage sites of the Philippines, including sea territories:\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left\"\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n|-\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#abcdef;\"| Region\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#abcdef;\"| Attractions\n|- \n! [[Ilocos Region]]\n| [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Ilocandia]] (includes [[Paoay Church]], UNESCO World Heritage Site and [[Santa Maria Church]], UNESCO World Heritage Site) \u2022 [[Vigan]], UNESCO World Heritage Site \u2022 [[Bolinao, Pangasinan|Bolinao]] \u2022 Heritage Railways and Stations of Luzon \u2022 [[Spanish Colonial Fortifications of the Philippines]] \u2022 [[Laoag]]\n|-\n! [[Cordillera Administrative Region]]\n| [[Rice Terraces of the Philippine Cordilleras]], UNESCO World Heritage Site \u2022 [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Cordillera]] \u2022 [[Kabayan Mummies|Kabayan Mummy Burial Caves]] \u2022  Alab Petroglyphs \u2022 [[Mount Pulag]] \u2022 [[Baguio City]], UNESCO Creative City \u2022 [[Lubuagan]] \u2022 [[Kiangan]] \u2022 [[Sagada]] \u2022 [[Balbalasang-Balbalan National Park]] \u2022 [[Cassamata Hill National Park]] \u2022 [[Mount Data National Park]]\n|-\n! [[Cagayan Valley]]\n| [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Cagayan Valley]] (including [[Tumauini Church]]) \u2022 [[Batanes]] \u2022 [[Lal-lo and Gattaran Shell Middens]] \u2022 [[Sierra Madre (Philippines)|Sierra Madre Range]] \u2022 Penablanca Petrographs \u2022 Paleolithic Archaeological Sites in Cagayan Valley (including Awidon Mesa Formation and Callao Limestone Formation) \u2022 [[Benham Rise|Kalipung-awan (Philippine) Rise]]\n|-\n! [[Central Luzon]]\n| [[Malolos]] \u2022 [[Baler]] \u2022 [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Central Luzon]] \u2022 [[Mount Pinatubo]] \u2022 [[Sierra Madre (Philippines)|Sierra Madre Range]] \u2022 [[Zambales Mountains]] \u2022 Heritage Railways and Stations of Luzon \u2022 [[San Fernando, Pampanga|San Fernando]] \u2022 [[Spanish Colonial Fortifications of the Philippines]] \u2022 Bataan Monuments on World War II \u2022 [[Pampanga]] Sugar Central Sites \u2022 Historic Rice Plantations of Tarlac (including [[Hacienda Luisita]]) \u2022 [[Benham Rise|Kalipung-awan (Philippine) Rise]] \u2022 [[Candaba Swamp]] \u2022 [[Subic Bay|Subic]] \u2022 [[Angeles City]] \u2022 [[Minalungao National Park]]\n|-\n! [[Metro Manila]]\n| [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Manila]] (including [[San Agustin Church (Manila)|San Agustin Church]], UNESCO World Heritage Site, [[Tondo Church]], [[Binondo Church]], [[Quiapo Church]], [[San Sebastian Church (Manila)|San Sebastian Church]], [[Malate Church]], [[Santa Ana Church]], and [[Ermita Church]]) \u2022 [[Intramuros]] \u2022 [[Rizal Park]] (including the [[National Museum of the Philippines]], [[Rizal Monument]], and the [[National Library of the Philippines]]) \u2022 [[University of Santo Tomas]] \u2022 Heritage Railways and Stations of Luzon \u2022 [[Spanish Colonial Fortifications of the Philippines]] \u2022 National Monuments of Manila (including the [[People Power Monument]]) \u2022 [[Las Pi\u00f1as-Para\u00f1aque Critical Habitat and Ecotourism Area]], Ramsar Wetland Site\n|-\n! [[Calabarzon]]\n| [[Taal, Batangas|Taal]] \u2022 [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Calabarzon]] \u2022 [[Kawit, Cavite|Kawit]] \u2022 [[Sariaya]] \u2022 [[Tayabas]] \u2022 [[Sierra Madre (Philippines)|Sierra Madre Range]] \u2022 [[Angono Petroglyphs]] \u2022 [[Limestone tombs of Kamhantik]] \u2022 [[Mount Makiling]], ASEAN Heritage Park \u2022 Heritage Railways and Stations of Luzon \u2022 [[Mount Banahaw]] \u2022 [[Spanish Colonial Fortifications of the Philippines]] \u2022 [[Corregidor]] \u2022 [[Benham Rise|Kalipung-awan (Philippine) Rise]] \u2022 [[Pagsanjan Falls]]\n|-\n! [[Bicol Region]]\n| [[Mayon Volcano]] \u2022 [[Ticao Island]] Cultural Landscape \u2022 [[Baroque Churches of the Philippines|Churches of Bicolandia]] (including Daraga Church) \u2022 [[Mount Isarog]] \u2022 Whale-shark Congregation Areas in the Philippines (including [[Donsol]]) \u2022 Heritage Railways and Stations of Luzon \u202